data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire manual `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` construction no longer compiles. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — no expression tree needed
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes that generate migrations

**a) Duplicate property names are uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF 10 appends a number to disambiguate. A migration will rename columns.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to `BillingAddress_City`; now it becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin the old names explicitly so no rename migration is generated:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sb =>
    {
        sb.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, sb =>
    {
        sb.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, pb =>
    {
        pb.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, ab =>
        {
            ab.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, etc.) now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Your code won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL for safe logging
{
    // Use logCommandText for log output (constants may be redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for the actual SQL
}
```

Update **all** methods in the interface — `CommandScalarExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, etc. — the same way.
